<header class="header">
  <div class="logo">
    <%= link_to root_path do %>
    <h1>Recognized.io</h1>
    <% end %>
  </div>
    <div class="banner-text">
      <h2>Revenue Recognition for <%= image_tag "stripe-logo.png", class: "stripe-logo"%></h2>
      <h3>If your SaaS company is using subscription billing, you are most likely
        over reporting your revenue. Find out how to properly recognize your revenue
        by signing up for early access.</h3>
      <a class="beta-button" href="#signup">Let me know when the Beta version is ready!</a>
    </div>
</header>

<section class="common-problem">
  <div class=common-problem-text>
    <h3>A Common Problem</h3>
    <div>
      <h4>Anniversary billing is convenient for your customers, but if your company
        is not accounting for it properly you could be forced to retroactively
        change your books to comply with new SEC regulations.</h4>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="trusted-solution">
  <div class="solution-text">
    <h3>A Trusted Solution</h3>
    <h4>By simply connecting your Stripe and QuickBooks accounts to <span class="company-name">Recognized.io</span>,
      you will be able to fully automate your revenue accounting.</h4>
      <div class="trusted-lower-text">
        <p>You will have a fully automated solution to deal with complicated
          events such as trials, discounts, and plan changes.</p>
      </div>
  </div>

  <div class="demo-space">
    <div class="demo-pic-border">
      <%= image_tag "demo-pic.jpg", class: "demo-pic" %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="a-try" id="signup">
  <form accept-charset="UTF-8" action="https://formkeep.com/f/80602264b68e" method="POST">
      <input type="hidden" name="utf8" value="âœ“">
    <h3>Let me know when the Beta version is ready!</h3>
    <div class="try-form">
      <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your Name">
      <input type="text" name="company" placeholder="Company">
      <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Email">
    </div>
    <div class="submit-button">
      <button>Submit</button>
    </div>
  </form>
</section>

